Floyd was expected to intensify, and it was unlikely to hit land soon.
The hurricane itself was likely to pass well north of the islands, meteorologists said.
It was too early to tell if the storm would threaten the Bahamas, which lie far north of other Caribbean islands.
Still, it was recommended that people along the U.S. southeast monitor the storm's course this weekend.
In Anguilla, the government closed schools Friday and residents put up hurricane shutters, in case the storm veered in their direction.
